The Moving Church.
On his appointment to Biggin Hill in 1951, Rev Vivian Symons had the vision to bring the materials for a new church building from the disused All Saints, North Peckham. But first, he had to deconstruct a huge Victorian church, and bring it by himself to its new site.
However, St Mark's is Grade 2 listed, not because of its origin, but due to its style.
properties.name: St Mark's Church, Biggin Hill

properties.description: We are delighted to present this spectacular extension and refurbishment project in Wanstead. The new side infill extension has a faceted geometry with a roof that rises up to meet a skylight at its highest point. An expanded bronze anodised mesh wraps around the existing building like a parasite. This fascinating geometry is achieved using a timber frame construction.
properties.name: The Pinehouse Parasite

properties.description: The Green is an underutilized natural asset located at the heart of Edmonton Green Town Centre. The Pavilion, co-designed with the local community plays a crucial role in supporting the proactive use of the space and fosters a stronger connection to the area. This initiative informs The Green's long-term vision through ideas and feedback gathered from a programme of community led activities.
properties.name: Pavilion on The Green

properties.description: The Community Centre at Christ Church Highbury, Islington N5, close to Highbury Fields, was designed by Matthew Lloyd Architects, and was completed in 2022. The centre was designed in close consultation with the church and local people and provides accessible, high quality, flexible spaces, church offices and a cafe, enabling the church to better meet and serve the local community.

images.title: Community centre, welcoming parish office and cafe, opening Christ Church to the local community.
View of the new community building from Highbury Fields

properties.name: Christ Church Community Centre, Highbury

properties.description: A transformative project to open up Cockpit for the benefit its makers and the local community. Our proposal for the redevelopment of Cockpit’s studio building in Deptford was supported by the Mayor of London’s Good Growth Fund and the Stride partnership. Completed in early summer 2024, the project makes Cockpit more publicly accessible and creates new workshop and studio space for makers.

images.title: Cockpit Deptford, copyright Peter Landers Photography
The new studio and workshop building, copyright Max Creasy

properties.name: Cockpit Studios Deptford

properties.description: Wiggle Wonderland is a touring pavilion activated by artists and communities. Created by architectural designer Beau McCarthy and artist Lucy Grainge, the pavilion is a timber-framed, open-air gallery. From hosting live performances to workshops, each install of the pavilion evolves and is shaped by people and place, and collaboration and co-creation are core to the project.
properties.name: Wiggle Wonderland

properties.description: A high street shop, recently converted into a home with a continued, strengthened and adaptable relationship to its street - allowing the former shop floor to be used for commercial or public purposes when desired. Currently occupied as both home and architecture studio, the project was collaboratively self-built by its designers.
properties.name: Costa's Barbers

properties.description:
St Luke Woodside is a large, airy late Victorian church.
The fittings and art added over the 20th and into the 21st century tell the history of the Church of England in this part of London.

images.title: The Rood - Second World War Memorial
Icon of St Luke, commissioned for our 150th anniversary in 2022

properties.name: St Luke Woodside

properties.description:
Periscope is a spatial design agency focused on regenerative design and public architecture.

We welcome visitors to join us through a day of workshops and talks around some of the practice's recent works, stimulating conversations on green and blue infrastructures, master planning and urbanism, public realm and landscape.

images.title: Our Open Design Studio looks forward to welcome you all for a visit!

properties.name: Periscope

properties.description: A series of events celebrating Croydon's Central Library building and its unique design. Croydon's first central library was moved to the Clocktower buildings when they first opened in May 1896. It was one of the first public libraries with open access shelves and offered one of the UK's first Children’s Libraries.
properties.name: Croydon Central Library

properties.description:
Acme Propeller Factory on Childers Street in Deptford is a 1920’s former ship propeller foundry. It has been home to artists since 1990. Currently, its 70,492 square feet of studio space is divided into 135 studio units, with 180 artists working in them over four floors.

The building is also home to The Acme Archive, the Acme Window Gallery and our public community and engagement space.

images.title: An aerial view of Acme Propeller Factory, 165 Childers Street, January 2024 © Acme.

properties.name: Acme Propeller Factory

properties.description: Step into the historic charm of 81 Columbia Road Flower Market in East London.  This iconic Victorian terraced house functions as a space for a local artist who has focussed on photographs of London architecture and life.
properties.name: 81 Columbia Road

properties.description:
A short cycle tour of Pollard Thomas Edwards' social housing projects in Islington - including RIBA Award winning Dover Court Estate. 

If you would like to book a ticket we ask you to consider donating £20 to Crisis - our charity partner as we celebrate our 50th Anniversary https://www.justgiving.com/page/pollardthomasedwards

images.title: Old Royal Free Square © Dennis Gilbert

properties.name: Islington Social Housing Cycle tour

properties.description: Built around a central green courtyard; the scheme completed for Gateway Housing Association consists of 32 shared ownership homes; including 3-bedroom maisonettes and 3-wheelchair units and features an under-5s play area. Arched entrances to individual dwellings introduce a human scale and echo other features in the street. The parapet detail is a nod to the Victorian heritage of the area.
properties.name: Regent Place

properties.description:
A low-key, light-infused, beautiful transformation of a dark Victorian terrace in Walthamstow. 

Whittaker Parsons architecture studio has remodelled and extended the cottage, creating a bright contemporary home overlooking Ian Turkington's prairie garden.

The project was shortlisted for this year's Don't Move Improve Awards.
properties.name: Don't Move, Improve! - Flitch Cottage

properties.description: Deptford's history is mainly linked to the river, but it also has a rich musical and cultural heritage. This walking tour will explore the sounds of Deptford and New Cross, along the way telling the radical – and often tragic – history of this diverse area, from police clashes at the Moonshot Club to groundbreaking community arts projects at the Albany.

images.title: Public artwork commemorating the 1977 Battle of Lewisham

properties.name: New Cross and Deptford: a radical history through music

properties.description: Join an architect-led tours of the newly completed Norton Folgate development. Explore the newly enhanced public spaces, see how historic buildings have been brought back into use, and take a look within the buildings which will be home to the burgeoning tech and creative industries in the Spitalfields and Shoreditch area.
properties.name: Norton Folgate

properties.description: The Lesnes Estate, part of the Thamesmead 'town of tomorrow', is at threat of demolition, resulting in the dispossession of the diverse and vibrant working-class community that call the estate their home. Join housing campaigners and residents to celebrate the estate, go on tours of the area, and hear from speakers about the process of estate regeneration, and its impact on communities.

images.title: Campaigners and residents at the estate, April 2024.

properties.name: The Lesnes Estate - And the campaign to save it

properties.description: A short film of the 100 year history of the building covering its time as a school, wartime ARP station and British Restaurant and school dinners centre. Display boards and volunteers available to answer any questions or show people around the space.  Teas and coffees and cakes, commemorative brochures and mugs will be available for purchase. Live music of songs from the last 100 years.
properties.name: Mornington Hall

properties.description: Surman Weston has completed its first self-build project, Peckham House, in South London.  A resilient, characterful, and experiential family home, that reflects our personalities and architectural interests.
properties.name: Peckham House

properties.description: Photographer Rachel Adams has been commissioned to create an exhibition capturing Croydon's iconic architecture & portraits of the people who look after these buildings, such as cleaners, concierge, security guards. The exhibition will be held here, at the Croydon Clocktower atrium & also at the Croydon Urban Room, located in the Whitgift Shopping Centre. For more information on visiting this exhibition at the Croydon Urban Room, head here: https://programme.openhouse.org.uk/listings/12687
properties.name: Croydon Unlocked

properties.description: Join South East London Community Energy for a walking tour of two community energy sites and a workshop on how community energy can help future-proof our city.

images.title: Our directors and the Lord Mayor of Greenwich on the roof of Mulgrave School

properties.name: South East London Community Energy - Walking Tour

properties.description: Designed by Langstaff Day Architects, The Corner House is a self-build, low energy sustainable CLT home on a constrained brownfield site in Stoke Newington overlooking Butterfield Green.

images.title: The Corner House - due to complete in September 2024 - overlooking Butterfield Green on Milton Grove
View during construction from Butterfield Green

properties.name: The Corner House

properties.description:
Find out more about Peckham's Aylesham Community Action group's work, get a sense of our neighbourhood's character on a walk with locals and discuss our campaigns against attempts for insensitive overdevelopments in our area.
We want to engage with built environment enthusiasts and together find some answers to London's critical questions : ‘What it takes to build or destroy a community?'
properties.name: A walk in Peckham's Aylesham Centre --- past and future

properties.description: The early 1800's saw the green fields of northern Clerkenwell spring up into grand squares and terraced houses. This walking tour will look at how the speculative housing developed, what remains today, and the unique stories and characters of the area.
properties.name: Georgian Clerkenwell's speculative housing boom

properties.description: Trade and craft associations have flourished for many centuries. The City of London companies, now collectively known as the Livery, are unique in their survival, number and diversity. The social and economic conditions which gave birth to the original guilds have long since been overtaken by the development of industry and commerce, but the livery companies still flourish today.
properties.name: The Butcher, The Baker and The Candlestick Maker

properties.description: London's skyline is rapidly growing! But 'skyscrapers' have been with us for millennia.  Join Ben Eley on a walking tour of London's most iconic skyscraper cluster – the ancient commercial heart of the City of London.  This tour considers the many social and economic influences which have pushed buildings higher, reflects on campaigns which seek to curtail tall building aspirations, and focusses in on some of London's most famous skyscrapers.
properties.name: London's skyscrapers walking tour

properties.description:
Feeling uninspired by your neighbourhood? Compete with others to explore and rethink your city.

To play Run The City you just need Instagram and energy! Respond to live challenges by being the first to post. Race against wit, intellect and sheer curiosity to better understand your surroundings.

Investigate how much of the city is open for the public. Be curious and uncover more of London!

images.title: Run The City played via Instagram

properties.name: Run The City

properties.description:
City of London was founded by Romans nearly 2000 years ago.  During its existence there were many heroes, but also some villains.  Over the years many murders, hangings and executions took place here. During this tour you will visit some of these sites to learn about the good, the bad and the ugly. 
Sherlock Holmes, William Wallace. Bloody Mary  and more...
properties.name: Heroes and Villains in the City

properties.description:
The University of East London’s Architecture and Visual Arts is a lively School that combines, Architecture, Physical Design and the Visual Arts. This perfect combination of creative programmes cross-pollinate, providing a fertile ground for creation, arts and design.
Our presence  will feature guided tours to the state-of-the-art facilities, creative studios, and ‘Way out East’ gallery.
properties.name: University of East London - Architecture and Visual Art

properties.description: Soho is a unique neighbourhood of creativity and diversity. Join us at the former Warner Brothers De Lane Lea studio at 75 Dean Street, home of the Museum of Soho and the Westminster LGBT+ Forum. Explore an exhibition of Soho's creativity and enjoy Soho short films in our cinema.
properties.name: De Lane Lea Studios, 75 Dean Street

properties.description: A walk through the City of London from the Thames (at the pool of London) up to Lloyds of London, site of the former HQ of the East India Company, looking at buildings and architecture built during the time of British Empire.

images.title: The two cities of London: stone and steel! (Credit: Natalie Chalk)

properties.name: Empire City walking tour

properties.description: Come and discover work by some of the UK’s top artists – from internationally acclaimed names to new and emerging talent. See behind the scenes of a working studio, meet artists, photographers, designers, illustrators and all sorts of creative people face to face and buy works of art directly from their studio.
properties.name: Martello Street Artist Open Studios

properties.description: Come and discover work by some of the UK’s top artists – from internationally acclaimed names to new and emerging talent. See behind the scenes of a working studio, meet artists, photographers, designers, illustrators and all sorts of creative people face to face and buy works of art directly from their studio.
properties.name: The Triangle Artist Open Studios

properties.description: A chance to see behind the scenes of working artists' studios, this SPACE building is home to glass and lighting makers, ceramicists, fine artists and the London Embroidery Studio.
properties.name: Timber Wharf Artist Open Studios

properties.description: Visit the life long home of Edward Augustus Bowles, one of the 20th century's great gardeners, that was restored by  Heritage Lottery Fund in 2011 to tell the story of the famous botanist’s life and gardening style.
properties.name: Myddelton House Gardens

properties.description: Appleby Blue  is a a contemporary social housing project reimagining the almshouse. Designed by Stirling Prize-winning architects Witherford Watson Mann for United St Saviour's Charity and located in Bermondsey, this innovative development offers 57 almshouses for residents aged 65+, fostering intergenerational connections and promoting community-centric urban living.
properties.name: Appleby Blue

properties.description:
There has been a Bakers' Hall on our current site since 1505.  The current incarnation dates from 1964, and is a unique collaboration of old and new.

The hall was originally designed by Trehearne and Norman, Preston and Partners in conjunction with Past Master William Newcome- Wright) and is the first of the post-war [World War II] livery halls in a Modernist idiom.
properties.name: Bakers' Hall

properties.description: St James's Piccadilly is a Grade I listed Christopher Wren church in the heart of the West End. Completed in 1684, and known as the Artists' Church, its interiors include historic works of art by Grinling Gibbons (reredos, organ case and font), postwar Classical interiors by Albert Richardson, and contemporary art by Che Lovelace honouring the 18th-century abolitionist Quobna Ottobah Cugoano.

images.title: St James's Church Piccadilly, seen from Jermyn Street
The lime wood reredos carved by Grinling Gibbons
The River (left) and Passage (right) by Che Lovelace hanging in the narthex at St James's Piccadilly

properties.name: St James's Piccadilly

properties.description: Winner of the 2024 'Don't Move Improve' award for best project under £100k A self build 38m2 triangular micro home converted from a former mechanic's garage,  creating a flexible and multifunctional home fit for living and working in.  Come and see sliding beds, triangular sofas and a pocket garden.

images.title: Street view of the Triangle House - a converted mechanic's garage
Triangle House: Winner of the 2024 'Don't Move, Improve!' prize for best project under 100k
Inverted bay window filled with bamboo creates privacy and 'defensible space'  from the street
Aerial view of the Triangle House
Multifunctional bedroom and living space overlooking a private courtyard

properties.name: Don't Move, Improve! - Triangle House

properties.description: Farmers and Fletchers' Hall is one of the 44 Livery Halls in the City of London.  The Hall is the home to both the Worshipful Company of Fletchers, an ancient Livery Company and the Farmers, a modern Livery Company.  The  Worshipful Company of Fletchers will open it's doors to show members of the public some of the modern work of the Fletchers Livery, it's traditions and heritage.

images.title: The Home of the Worshipful Company of Farmers and the Worshipful Company of Fletchers.

properties.name: Farmers and Fletchers' Hall

properties.description: The Croydon Urban Room is a space to talk about the past, present and future of the Croydon town centre. Through conversa­tions, stories, exhibitions and events, the Urban Room brings together the views of those who live, work and visit the area to create a shared vision of the future and test new uses live in action.
properties.name: Croydon Urban Room

properties.description: Visit a secluded urban courtyard forming part of the transformation of a Grade II listed former pub
properties.name: Blockmakers Arms

properties.description: We're running guided walks in Tottenham Hale showcasing Haringey's new council homes and the council's commitment to working with residents on place-making and regeneration as part of our Haringey Deal. The walks start/end at Living Under One Sun in Down Lane Park, where there will be a display about our programme to build 3,000 new council homes by 2031 and our regeneration of Down Lane Park.

images.title: New council homes at Hale Wharf, with new bridge across River Lea
Walter Tull House, 131 new council homes in Tottenham Hale
First phase of co-designed improvements to Down Lane Park, Tottenham Hale

properties.name: Tottenham Hale & placemaking together

properties.description: Brockley Conservation Area's High Victorian enclave holds many interesting houses in a variety of styles, including Edwardian domestic architecture, historic trees and original lanes and mews. These have survived into the 21st century almost intact. Houses built in the 1950s and 1960s indicate WWII bomb damage and add to the area's variety and history.
properties.name: Architectural Walk in Brockley

properties.description: Discover Hackney’s exemplary contemporary residential projects on this inspiring walk through the Broadway Market and Graham Road & Mapledene conservation areas led by Hidden House Project. Explore how these projects' thoughtful design and development contribute positively to the public realm and the architectural diversity and richness of the area, shaping London Fields' future heritage.

images.title: Photo by Hidden House Project - London Fields, E8
Photo by Hidden House Project - Broadway Market, London Fields, E8
Photo by Hidden House Project - London Fields, E8

properties.name: Future Heritage: Contemporary Architecture in Hackney

properties.description: Blackhorse Lane Ateliers is London's only craft jeans maker. Based within a tastefully renovated 1920s factory building in Walthamstow. Join us for a behind-the-scenes tour where you will get to see the factory in operation. Find out about our methods of production, the equipment, tools and materials we work with and meet some of our team.
properties.name: Blackhorse Lane Ateliers

properties.description: thinkFOUND make socially and environmentally sustainable furniture. We represent a social value model that gives back to communities around London. From our workshop in the Argall Industrial Estate we incorporate carpentry, fabrication, upcycling, training, employment, coaching and more. Over the weekend we will be hosting an open studio demonstrating our processes and showcasing past work.
properties.name: thinkFOUND

properties.description: Take a tour of Armstrong Audio with engineers and owners, T & Shalma. Learn about its rich history dating back to 1932 when the company was established as 'Armstrong Wireless & Television Ltd.'. and began manufacturing public address systems, radios and televisions for public use in WWII.
properties.name: Armstrong Audio

properties.description:
Thousands of Hong Kongers have made Sutton their home in recent years. 

Join us on Saturday 21st September, 2024 as we celebrate Mooncake Festival with a community-led cultural programme:

- Enjoy traditional music and performances from Sutton Honger, Lion
Rock Kids Children's Choir, traditional Chinese music, pop
dances, and Acapella.
- Family activity
- A variety of drinks and snacks
properties.name: Mid-Autumn Festival Celebrations

properties.description: Hello! We're Throwley Yard Cinema, Sutton's independent cinema and cultural hub. With a strong focus on the local community, our four cinema screens are only part of a wider offering which also includes a café, bar, live events, DJ academy, socialising and much more.
properties.name: Throwley Yard Cinema

properties.description: A walking tour to see a number of co-designed projects completed by Haringey Council by working with Wood Green's local community. Including community parklets, two large murals, a new café, and the award winning Rising Green Youth Hub.
properties.name: Wood Green Placemaking Walking Tour

properties.description: Join us for the Wood Green Creative Spaces and Places Tour, a journey through the workspaces of the creative industries of Wood Green. This tour offers a unique opportunity to visit a few of Wood Green’s workspaces showcasing a range of studios such as those for ceramics, music, visual arts, and design.
properties.name: Wood Green Creative Spaces and Places Tour

properties.description:
We are offering people a rare glimpse of the birthplace of television with guided tours of Studios A & B. 
The BBC first arrived at the Palace in 1935, as the race to broadcast via the latest innovation in entertainment – television – gathered pace. The corporation leased the entire East Wing of the Palace, with former dining rooms transformed into Studios.

images.title: Alexandra Palace, Studio B, Control Gallery, July 1946

properties.name: Historic BBC Studio Tours

properties.description: Join us for a walking tour of the large-scale murals and Grade II listed mosaic mural  on Broadwater Farm Estate, commissioned in the 1980s in the wake of riots on the estate. Visit the mosaic restoration facility on the estate to hear from conservation professionals, get up close to local community art, see restoration techniques and learn about the history and future of the mosaic mural.

images.title: Equality-Harmony Mural on Tangmere, Broadwater Farm Estate

properties.name: Broadwater Farm Estate - Murals and Mosaics Tour

properties.description: Discover the work of innovative charity Furnishing Futures, which partners with the interiors industry to create trauma-informed healing homes for families given empty social housing after escaping domestic abuse. Enjoy a tour of our warehouse and studio, meet our team and learn about sustainability in interiors and the impact of trauma-informed design for recovery.
properties.name: Furnishing Futures Open Studio: Meet the charity

properties.description: Join us for an alcohol-free beer tasting and brewery tour! Our shutter will be open all afternoon for you to pop in and join us for a beer. Our brewer James will lead a brewery-tour session at 2pm giving the low-down on the magic behind alcohol-free brewing, followed by a guided tasting with a selection of four great Nirvana beers.
properties.name: Nirvana Brewery

properties.description: Enter the world of the curious with a special meet the maker open day at the UK's first ever Absinthe Distillery. Learn about the origins and rituals of this once illicit liquor from distiller and co-founder Rhys Everett.
properties.name: Devil’s Botany Distillery

properties.description:
This world-renowned actor training school took up residence in Grange Court in 1969.
Grange Court is the heart of DSL (Drama Studio London). It's a large Victorian house and home to acting studios, a theatre, a sound studio, a library, costume wardrobe, prop store and a small secluded garden.
properties.name: Drama Studio London

properties.description: Overhaul of an ex-local authority home in Islington with a new timber cloister that encircles a hidden courtyard and a series of unexpected spaces that pirouette around a triangular column.  Access to 12 Davey Close via passage next to 48 Arundel Square
properties.name: Pirouette House

properties.description: Richard Griffiths Architects is a multi-award winning practice specializing in the Heritage Conservation of old buildings and new build within an historic context.  The practice is opening the office to people who are interested to learn more about our work and projects.  There will be also presentations from specialists in the field of conservation throughout the day.
properties.name: Architect's Studio - Richard Griffiths Architects

properties.description: Upper maisonette remodelled to create a spacious top floor open-plan living space. Bespoke kitchen, dining and lounge furniture. Full height doors and a Dougls Fir stair screen
properties.name: 130 Drayton Park

properties.description: Step inside the Climpson & Son's Coffee Roastery and see the inner workings of where your favourite coffee gets sourced and roasted.
properties.name: Climpson & Sons Coffee Roastery

properties.description: Join us for a special open day at Kribi Coffee UK! Owners Anne and Luca will guide you on a tour through the air roastery and share the rich story of Cameroonian coffee and their family’s connection to the farmers and the land. There will be live demonstrations of the coffee air roaster and some sample coffee to try!
properties.name: Kribi Coffee Roastery

properties.description: Oru Sutton is a landmark workspace, leisure, and destination space in the heart of Sutton High Street, creating a nurturing environment for people to connect and thrive in their work and personal lives.
properties.name: Oru Space

properties.description:
The Trampery Wood Green is host to 50 artists currently occupying studios in the building. At our open day event you will have the opportunity to come and see their work and their workspaces!
As part of the open day we will activate the space by hosting multiple activities in the lounge throughout the event. For this we are planning on having an agenda of skill-sharing, music and food and drinks.
properties.name: The Trampery Wood Green

properties.description: On the surface Thamesmead might seem concrete and grey, but on this tour we will take a look at the colour and life local artists that are breathing into the area. Examining the past and present, we'll explore the abbey ruins, exciting sculptures, concrete skywalks, and vivid murals that make this place the Town of Tomorrow.

images.title: Earth Mother's Shade mural by Gary Drostle
Children overlooking Southmere lake, 1973. Bexley Local Studies & Archive Centre from TMCA
GLC postcard: Playground on Tavy Bridge 1975. (c) TMCA
Thamesmead Codex by Bob and Roberta Smith. Photgraphed at Tate Modern

properties.name: Art and architecture in Thamesmead

properties.description:
A walk visiting 5 historic chapels and churches in Tower Hamlets.
Saturday 21 Sept, meeting at 9.55am.

images.title: Chapel at the Royal Foundation of St Katharine

properties.name: East London Chapels & Churches Walk

properties.description: Explore twenty first century architecture in one of London's most luxurious and historic neighbourhoods. This walking tour covers Mayfair's new contemporary developments, discovering architectural treasures, hidden gems and buildings that are designed for our changing climate.
properties.name: Distinctly Mayfair walking tour

properties.description: Visitors are invited to a descriptive tour of the Rewind: This is Croydon's Music.
properties.name: Audio-Described & Touch Tour of Rewind Exhibition

properties.description: An opportunity to explore our permanent “Home of Ideas” and to visit our current exhibition “Ideas Aren’t Linear” – a non-linear journey through the design processes of two recently completed projects: The Energy Hub and Aylesbury Health Centre, known affectionately as “The Elephant and The Castle” – exposing the twists, about-turns and serendipity that informed their unexpected relationship.
properties.name: Ideas Aren’t Linear

properties.description: Although Highgate is labelled a sleepy 'village for millionaires' frozen in time, during our two-hour walk with an integrated cardio effect, participants will see how this area has evolved under the influence of generations of nonconformists. Our route includes one of the most architecturally diverse street in London, experimental pink plaques and eccentric homes.

images.title: Highpoint II, North Hill, London N6
The Boogaloo, Archway Rd, London N6
Studio, Duke's Head Yard (1940) by Tayler & Green for cartoonist Roger Pettiward

properties.name: Nonconformity in Highgate

properties.description: Take a guided tour of a beautiful example of a Wren church with unique features

images.title: St Margaret Pattens from the South door

properties.name: St Margaret Pattens Guild Church

properties.description: VATRAA's fibre-reinforced concrete extension to a Victorian house in London Fields is a project about materials, light and views. On the inside, the rough concrete floor, bench and worktop are balanced by oak and a jute fabric inspired by the client's art collection. On the outside, a fibre-reinforced external leaf reduced the concrete amount by 40% compared to a regular steel reinforcement.
properties.name: London Fields extension

properties.description: This walking tour will draw comparisons between the progress and demise of the postwar welfare state. Focusing on housing and healthcare, the tour will present prominent examples from the era  and discuss ways these are being adapted to meet contemporary challenges, such as the housing crisis and ongoing maintenance. The ambition of the tour is to reassess the value of postwar architecture today.

images.title: A collage of the mix of building we will see across the walk

properties.name: Postwar and post-welfare North London walking tour

properties.description: Join SAVE Britain’s Heritage and Klaud Studio on a tour of the prestigious Sprüth Magers art gallery in Mayfair. Learn about the history of this seven-storey grade II listed townhouse designed by Sir Robert Taylor and witness Klaud's sensitive and sustainable restoration work. Damage from earlier renovations was corrected and a multi-use space created: a commercial gallery, a workshop and offices.
properties.name: Georgian Grafton Street: Sprüth Magers Gallery

properties.description: Up in Smoke - the NOW Gallery Design Commission by artist John Booth and architecture studio CAN, transforms the gallery into a vibrant installation that reveals the rich history of Greenwich Peninsula, through its iconic chimneys. The exhibition combines the duo's distinctive styles: Booth's playful, colourful design aesthetic and CAN's fresh, irreverent approach to architecture.
properties.name: Up in Smoke by John Booth X CAN

properties.description: Join us for an exclusive architect and designer led tour of The Black Horse Bar & Pizzeria. Hear directly from the architect and interior designer from Pencil & Brick and Flamingo & Oak about their inspiration and creative process behind designing this award-nominated venue. Discover the design elements that make The Black Horse unique and gain insights into their work.
properties.name: The Black Horse

properties.description: Join us and learn more about the ancient art of patination. Celebrate 35 years of Capisco by delving into our sample archive and a gallery of our projects. Our master patination technicians will also be on hand to demonstrate some classic techniques.
properties.name: Capisco Metal Patination Workshop

properties.description: Every hour on the hour Neckstamper will give a brewery tour explaining our brewing process and equipment we use. The brewery taproom will also be open for the public to enjoy our beer or purchase cans to take away.
properties.name: Neckstamper Brewery

properties.description: Alfies Antique Market is London's largest indoor antique and vintage market. The market celebrates 90 dealers who each boast uniquely sourced antique and vintage items.
properties.name: Alfies Antique Market

properties.description: Once a Victorian arboretum, Abney Park Cemetery, part of London's Magnificent Seven, was revitalised with National Heritage Lottery funding in 2021. The renovation restored the chapel and main entrance, creating a vibrant workshop space for London-based art and design collective, WAX Atelier. During Open House, WAX Atelier will showcase innovative projects in their unique workspace amidst the park

images.title: WAX Atelier’s ‘lab’ studio and exhibition space

properties.name: WAX Atelier within Abney Park

properties.description: The Valley Room is a research and project space created by AiR. It considers artist-making in the Lea Valley through a gathering of artefacts, films, objects, maps, books. Monthly openings highlight one artwork, with the artist making an intervention or exhibition.
properties.name: Skyline Soundscape at The Valley Room, AiR

properties.description: The Old Vestry Office is a Grade II listed building that was built in the early 19th century. It was originally created as a Beadle's office but later used as a police station, containing 2 cells. The Old Enfield Charitable Trust - an independent charity serving those living and working within the boundary of the Ancient Parish - run their services from the Old Vestry Office.
properties.name: Royal Charter to the hidden prison cell of Enfield

properties.description: Angel Yard is a versatile and creative communal hub. Located within Snell's Park in Edmonton, it provides a place for people to develop and share their skills, whilst enriching the community and strengthening social bonds, as people from diverse backgrounds come together to collaborate and learn.
properties.name: Transforming Trash to Treasure: Upcycling Workshop

properties.description: Join us on a guided walk following the  'Tottenham Tales' trail. Tottenham has a rich and fascinating tapestry of tales of local rebels, artists, pioneers and more. The tour will take us around South Tottenham, a treasure hunt for the new Tottenham Tale signage that highlights the buildings and sites that hold remnants of these tales, supported by an online map to bring archive material to life.
properties.name: Tottenham Tales Walk

properties.description: Join a City Guide to explore the stories of queer monarchs; the Cathedral convenience; erotic theatre; cross-dressers and find out what Henry VIII had to do with it all.
properties.name: From Prejudice to Pride

properties.description: It began with wool and ended in wildness. This tour with a City Guide will uncover 800 years of history and happenings associated with the incident-packed Bartholomew Fair.
properties.name: Bartholomew Fair

properties.description:
In our House, creativity is a way of life. Warehouse Art Collective forges friendships and art under one roof. Artists who call this craftwork factory home have a lot in common, while exploring ideas and artistic visions with various materials and mediums.
The public can witness the artistic process and engage with contemporary art in the work/live industrial unit within Haringey Warehouse District.
properties.name: Warehouse Art Collective

properties.description: Join us for a hard-hat visit exploring the literal foundations of Britain's first permanent Migration Museum, opening in the City of London in 2027/8. Find out about our 12-year journey to build Britain’s missing museum, our exciting plans for our permanent home, and discover some of the rich migration histories that surround the site.

properties.name: Site-tours of Britain's first Migration Museum

properties.description: Myddelton House Gardens were once home to Edward Augustus Bowles, one of Britain’s most famous self-taught gardeners, artists and expert botanists. The gardens are a treasure trove of hidden gems and the beautifully reconstructed Victorian Glasshouse is no exception.
properties.name: Music with Plants by the Glasshouse

properties.description: Dow Jones Architects has recently refurbished this 1866 listed schoolhouse as their architecture studio. The project has created a light-filled contemporary work space, and demonstrates a sensitive, low carbon approach to an historic restoration.
properties.name: St Marks Schoolhouse

properties.description:
London is the ultimate urban sprawl. But hiding among the buildings and cars there are an estimated eight million trees. So who else do we share our city with? Do you have a neighbourhood goose? Are there really seals in the River Thames? 

Join Lucy Brown from wildlife conservation charity ZSL on a journey through London's wild alter-ego, via the parks and waterways of Camden and Westminster.

properties.description: Join a captivating journey through the City of London with our exclusive Muslim Heritage Tour. Discover the deep connections of Salahuddin Ayubi and marvel at the UK's oldest Muslim statues, dating back 1000 years. Uncover the legacy of England’s most famous Middle Eastern immigrant and delve into fascinating tales of crime and health in history.
properties.name: Muslim Heritage of the City tour

properties.description: Come and explore the Isokon collection and workshop and learn more about our manufacturing processes. Experience the techniques and materials that are used to craft our collection which spans over 90 years of modernist and contemporary furniture design.

properties.description:
Morden College is a charity dedicated to supporting older people, founded in 1695 by the pioneering merchant, Sir John Morden.

The original 1695 Grade I listed Quadrangle by Edward Strong, Sir Christopher Wren's master stonemason, has provided older people with accommodation for over 300 years. Across the site and beautiful grounds, the John Morden Centre, a new community space, won the RIBA Stirling prize in 2023.
properties.name: The John Morden Centre and Morden College Almshouses

properties.description: This four double-bedroom Victorian terraced home sits on a quiet, tree-lined residential street between Clapton and Stoke Newington. A comprehensive restoration and extension project by Partner London artfully balances the restored original features with natural, sympathetic materials and considered details to create a home well-suited to modern lifestyles within the original Victorian fabric.

images.title: Partner London, photograph by Richard Oxford

properties.name: Walsingham Road

properties.description: Southall Manor House is a Grade II* Listed Tudor building - the oldest building in Southall and potentially one of the oldest surviving buildings in West London. The building underwent recent refurbishment, extension and landscaping from 00 Architects. For Open House, the building's heritage will be animated by scents from perfumers 420Tuesdays and Kushbu.
properties.name: Southall Manor House

properties.description: Muphoria Gallery based on Berwick Street, Soho, is London's first music art gallery, exhibiting pop art and musical instruments created by UK artists. We will be hosting a walking tour around the musically important buildings of Soho.
properties.name: Muphoria Gallery

properties.description: A revival and love letter to London’s lost bohemia..   Travel back in time to the legendary haunt of some of Soho's greatest creatives.   Featuring pictures, press cuttings and even the piano from the much loved private members club.
properties.name: Explore the authentically recreated Colony Room

properties.description: Come and join us to explore this historic market and its evolution.   View images of it's historic past and its part in bringing us such exotic items as tomatoes, olive oil and grapefruit.  Take a photograph from the same spot to recreate Oasis's iconic What's the story? (Morning Glory)  album cover.  Information point and advice on exploring other Soho Open House locations and events.
properties.name: Berwick Street Market

properties.description: Start your exploration of the Open House Soho Neighbourhood with a shot of coffee, a refreshing cold drink and a bite to eat.  Explore our newly installed timeline of Soho, and our existing display on the church's history.   Relax in our calm and welcoming gardens.  Starting point for the Creative Soho Walking Tours.
properties.name: Sacred Grounds / St Anne's Church and Garden

properties.description: Architectural showspace on the first floor of a duplex unit in the City’s Royal Exchange (the ground floor houses clothing boutique, GOFF COURTNEY, which also sells accessories, visual books & magazines. INTERMISSION is exhibiting three-dimensional artworks by architect Misha Stefan and RE:PLACE – proposing alternative, more inclusive destinations for three prominent gateway sites in the City.

properties.name: Intermission

properties.description: Come visit us at Gather, a hot glass studio in Charlton / Woolwich for an open studio day. On Saturday 21st September, we are running a number of pre-book short, exciting classes where participants will 'blow their own bauble' for £55 each. At 3pm we will host a free studio tour with glass blowing demonstrations. Visit us see the process in action!
properties.name: Glassblowing open studio

properties.description: Former 19th century ale house now a spacious modernised residential building in the historic centre of Greenwich
properties.name: The Earl Grey

properties.description: The North Arch Arts Space invites you to explore their artist's work and exhibitions in a redesigned spatial framework by A347. Inspired by the railway arch structure, these flexible, partitionable spaces adapt to artists' needs, offering a dynamic environment for creating, showcasing, and engaging with the community. Discover Beck Road’s architectural heritage, meet the makers, and see their work
properties.name: North Arch Art Space

properties.description:
This is your invite to The Linkup! A space where young POC and those from working-class communities can connect, create and speak your truth.

At The Linkup, we'll dive into real conversations and create a collaborative mural that captures our experiences, our cultures and our vision for the future in London. This is your space to express, explore and inspire.
properties.name: The Link Up
